ASD 2025 Graduate Program

ASD Level 4

$74,796 - 77,787 (plus Super)

ACT, QLD, VIC, WA

  

** The Role **

As an ASD graduate, you will experience three four-month rotations that will
develop your skills and allow you to explore different areas of interest. You
will receive bespoke training and be mentored by leading experts in their
field. You will be encouraged to try new things, while working across
multidisciplinary teams that focus on critical intelligence matters.

Upon successful completion of the program, you will have a permanent role at
ASD that is relevant to your degree and interests.

Diversity powers our mission. Our work is challenging, and our history shows
that the best teams contain a diverse range of people. To achieve our mission,
we require people with strong integrity and a mix of skills, passion,
adaptability, resilience, curiosity and creativity.

We support our people to bring their best selves to work. Whether this is
through our diversity and inclusion initiatives, flexible working arrangements
or learning and development opportunities.

We are committed to the growth of our most important resource – you.

  

  

** About our Team **

** ** ASD is entering an exciting phase of growth, innovation and transformation. Our agency has committed to delivering [ REDSPICE ](https://www.asd.gov.au/sites/default/files/2022-05/ASD-REDSPICE-Blueprint.pdf) , which is the most significant single investment in the Australian Signals Directorate’s 75 years. 

ASD is seeking applications from highly talented graduates having recently
completed a Bachelor Degree, recognised in Australia, or who are currently
completing their final year of tertiary study to enter the agency during this
unprecedented period of growth.

  

** Our Ideal Candidate **

** ** Your degree doesn’t define your career at ASD, we are looking for graduates from almost every discipline, with opportunities in areas including: 

  

  * [ Accounting and Finance ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/accounting-and-finance)
  * [ Administration and Customer Service ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/administration-and-customer-service)
  * [ Auditing, Assurance and Fraud Control ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/audit-assurance-and-fraud-control)
  * [ Cyber Security ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/cyber-security)
  * [ Engineering and Technical ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/engineering-and-technical)
  * [ Human Resources ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/human-resources)
  * [ Information and Communications Technology ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/information-and-communications-technology)
  * [ Information and Knowledge Management ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/information-and-knowledge-management)
  * [ Infrastructure ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/infrastructure)
  * [ Intelligence and analysis ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/intelligence)
  * [ Legal ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/legal)
  * [ Logistics ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/logistics)
  * [ Media and Communications ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/media-and-communication)
